description: Creates a new Amazon Redshift subnet group. You must provide a list of one or more subnets in your existing Amazon Virtual Private Cloud (Amazon VPC) when creating Amazon Redshift subnet group. For information about subnet groups, go to Amazon Redshift Cluster Subnet Groups in the Amazon Redshift Cluster Management Guide.

parameters.name: ClusterSubnetGroupName
parameters.description: The name for the subnet group. Amazon Redshift stores the value as a lowercase string. Constraints: Must contain no more than 255 alphanumeric characters or hyphens. Must not be 'Default'. Must be unique for all subnet groups that are created by your Amazon Web Services account. Example: examplesubnetgroup.

parameters.name: Description
parameters.description: A description for the subnet group.

parameters.name: SubnetIds
parameters.description: An array of VPC subnet IDs. A maximum of 20 subnets can be modified in a single request. (string) ---

parameters.name: Tags
parameters.description: A list of tag instances. (dict) --- A tag consisting of a name/value pair for a resource. Key (string) --- The key, or name, for the resource tag. Value (string) --- The value for the resource tag.

nested_params.name: Key
nested_params.description: The key, or name, for the resource tag.

nested_params.name: Value
nested_params.description: The value for the resource tag.

nested_items.name: ClusterSubnetGroupName

nested_items.name: SubnetGroupStatus
nested_items.description: The status of the cluster subnet group. Possible values are Complete, Incomplete and Invalid.

nested_items.name: SupportedClusterIpAddressTypes
nested_items.description: The IP address types supported by this cluster subnet group. Possible values are ipv4 and dualstack.
